cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning techniques to automatically capture 3D pose, shape, and texture of animals from images acquired in the wild. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses deep learning techniques and regression pipelines, which are common in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the problem of animal conservation, which falls under the sub-category cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper deals with texture synthesis, which is a common topic in the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia).
